6 cm)."},{"content":"Place chocolate biscuit, broken in pieces, and butter in mixing bowl then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>. Tip mixture into prepared tin, smooth surface and freeze until required. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Raspberry Coulis"},{"content":"Place raspberries, sugar and water (if using) in mixing bowl then, without measuring cup, cook <b>6 min\/90°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Strain through a fine sieve and set aside."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Cheesecake Filling"},{"content":"Preheat oven to 150°C."},{"content":"Place chocolate in mixing bowl and grate <b>6 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then melt <b>3-5 min\/50°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add double cream, cream cheese, sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong> and whip <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Pour mixture over prepared biscuit base. Dot with ⅓ raspberry coulis and create a marbled look by running a skewer through them.  Bake for 1 hour (150°C)."},{"content":"Turn oven off, prop oven door ajar and leave to cool inside for 1 hour, then chill in fridge for 12-24 hours."},{"content":"Serve with remaining raspberry coulis."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If you want to use frozen raspberries, omit the <b>1 tsp water<b> for the coulis."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","16h","12 portions"]}